# Atoms in this file are deliberately masked: the ebuild is shipped
# in the overlay (so you can pin to it if you know you want it) but
# does not get installed by default. Unmask any of them in your own
# /etc/portage/package.unmask/rato-verlay if you want to opt in.

# Ramin Torabi <16882282+RaminTorabi@users.noreply.github.com> (2026-04-25)
# CloudWatch Agent 1.300067.0 was tagged upstream but is not the
# release marked as latest stable (latest stable: 1.300066.1). Mask
# the newer tag so a default `emerge` keeps picking 1.300066.1; unmask
# explicitly if you want to track the upstream tag aggressively.
=app-admin/amazon-cloudwatch-agent-1.300067.0

# Ramin Torabi <16882282+RaminTorabi@users.noreply.github.com> (2026-05-05)
# amazon-efs-utils-bin is a prebuilt-binary repackaging of AWS's
# official AL2023 RPM. The source-build sibling (net-fs/amazon-efs-utils,
# 9999 live ebuild) is the default install path; the -bin variant is
# kept available for hosts that cannot afford a Rust + Python build.
# Unmask explicitly if -bin is what you want.
net-fs/amazon-efs-utils-bin
